---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Contact & Research Recruitment · KUNLING" description="Contact KUNLING and explore undergraduate, master’s, and PhD research opportunities in AI for Earth Science.">
  <section class="contact-hero">
    <div class="container contact-center" data-reveal>
      <span class="section-kicker">Connect</span>
      <h1>Start a conversation.</h1>
      <p>For research conversations, scientific collaboration, and open-source work, reach out through the channels below.</p>
      <a class="inline-link contact-join-link" href="#join-kunling">View student opportunities ↓</a>
      <div class="contact-orbits">
        <a href="mailto:liuze@ouc.edu.cn" aria-label="Email Ze Liu">
          <img src="/assets/icons/gmail.svg" alt="" />
          <span>Email</span>
        </a>
        <a href="https://github.com/Kunling-AI" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" aria-label="KUNLING on GitHub">
          <img src="/assets/icons/github.svg" alt="" />
          <span>GitHub</span>
        </a>
        <a href="https://cmg.ouc.edu.cn/2024/1227/c30164a492019/page.htm" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" aria-label="Official university profile">
          <img src="/assets/brand/kunling-logo.png" alt="" />
          <span>OUC</span>
        </a>
      </div>
      <div class="contact-address">
        <span>PRINCIPAL CONTACT</span>
        <strong>Ze Liu · Associate Professor</strong>
        <a href="mailto:liuze@ouc.edu.cn">liuze@ouc.edu.cn</a>
        <p>Ocean University of China · Qingdao, China</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="recruitment-section section-shell" id="join-kunling">
    <div class="container">
      <header class="section-heading split-heading" data-reveal>
        <div>
          <span class="section-kicker">Research recruitment</span>
          <h2>Study the Earth with intelligence.</h2>
        </div>
        <p>We welcome senior undergraduates, master’s students, and PhD students who want to explore the next generation of AI × ocean geology × Earth science research.</p>
      </header>

      <div class="opportunity-grid">
        <article class="opportunity-card" data-reveal>
          <span>01 · Senior undergraduates</span>
          <h3>Start with a real scientific question.</h3>
          <p>Build sustained research experience beyond a practice project, with clear questions, experiments, and research outputs.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="opportunity-card" data-reveal>
          <span>02 · Master’s students</span>
          <h3>Develop depth across disciplines.</h3>
          <p>Connect AI methods, scientific computing, and domain knowledge through a complete research workflow.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="opportunity-card" data-reveal>
          <span>03 · PhD students</span>
          <h3>Push an ambitious direction forward.</h3>
          <p>Develop AI-native research tools and scientific discoveries around challenging Earth-system questions.</p>
        </article>
      </div>

      <div class="candidate-panel" data-reveal>
        <span>Backgrounds we welcome</span>
        <p>Artificial intelligence · Computer science · Software engineering · Geophysics · Geology · Ocean science · Mathematics · Physics · Mechanics · Ecology · Biology · Geographic information science · Earth system science</p>
        <strong>You do not need to know everything at the start. Curiosity, sustained progress, and a willingness to learn matter most.</strong>
      </div>

      <div class="recruitment-detail-grid">
        <article class="recruitment-detail-card" data-reveal>
          <span class="section-kicker">What we look for</span>
          <h3>A strong foundation for research growth.</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Interest in AI, scientific computing, ocean geology, or Earth science.</li>
            <li>A working foundation in Python programming.</li>
            <li>Willingness to learn knowledge from emerging interdisciplinary fields.</li>
            <li>Capacity to commit consistent time to research training.</li>
            <li>Ability to learn independently, read literature, run experiments, or contribute to scientific writing.</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="recruitment-detail-card accent-card" data-reveal>
          <span class="section-kicker">Bonus experience</span>
          <h3>Useful skills—not prerequisites.</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>PyTorch or TensorFlow.</li>
            <li>Transformers, PINNs, neural operators, or LLM agents.</li>
            <li>Geophysics, ocean geology, structural geology, or ecological data analysis.</li>
            <li>Research papers, competitions, open-source projects, or a GitHub portfolio.</li>
            <li>GMT, PyGMT, PyVista, xarray, NetCDF, or GIS tools.</li>
            <li>Finite elements, finite differences, HPC, or Docker.</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
      </div>

      <section class="research-support-panel" data-reveal>
        <div>
          <span class="section-kicker">What you will gain</span>
          <h3>Research training from question to publication.</h3>
        </div>
        <ul>
          <li>Opportunities to participate in frontier AI for Science research projects.</li>
          <li>End-to-end training in problem decomposition, model design, experimental analysis, and scientific writing.</li>
          <li>Guidance from the supervisor and team on research ideas, technical routes, and writing.</li>
          <li>Opportunities to contribute to papers, patents, and open-source projects, with clear authorship based on individual contributions.</li>
          <li>Strong contributors may join SCI papers, academic conferences, or follow-on research projects.</li>
          <li><strong>Research reward support of approximately ¥2,000–6,000</strong>, depending on completion, team contribution, and project arrangements.</li>
          <li>Access to CPU/GPU computing, domestic and international foundation models, research accounts, data resources, and the team GitHub platform.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <div class="application-panel" data-reveal>
        <div>
          <span class="section-kicker">How to apply</span>
          <h3>Tell us what you want to explore.</h3>
          <p>If you want to contribute to a real exploration of future AI-native science—not only a practice project—we would like to hear from you.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="application-details">
          <p>Email <a href="mailto:kunlinghire@126.com?cc=liuze@ouc.edu.cn&amp;subject=KUNLING%20Research%20Application">kunlinghire@126.com</a> and CC <a href="mailto:liuze@ouc.edu.cn">liuze@ouc.edu.cn</a> with:</p>
          <ol>
            <li><span>01</span>Your CV or résumé.</li>
            <li><span>02</span>Your university, year of study, and major.</li>
            <li><span>03</span>The project direction that interests you.</li>
            <li><span>04</span>Relevant code, papers, competitions, course projects, or GitHub work.</li>
            <li><span>05</span>Your estimated weekly time commitment.</li>
          </ol>
          <a class="button light-button" href="mailto:kunlinghire@126.com?cc=liuze@ouc.edu.cn&amp;subject=KUNLING%20Research%20Application">Apply by email →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
